        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The correlator setup has been chosen to include the thre emission lines proposed to be observed. The line-free channels and one dedicated spw will be used to sample the continuum.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We propose better spatial resolution (0.2'') than previous observations (0.6'' FWHM) in order to contruct exceptional velocity maps and study/compare the dust and gas morphologies. Previous medium resolution interferometric observations suggest that our galaxies are smaller than 1'', which is the requested largest angular scale. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We base our requirements on the already observed $\rm ^{12}CO$ $J$= 1--0 transitions for G09.v10.124 and HXMM01, considering the faintest source: X01N in HXMM01. It has $S_{\rm CO(1-0)}^{\rm peak} = 0.48 \, {\rm mJy}$. The CO ladder varies significantly among SMGs (Carilli \&amp; Walter 2013; Riechers et al. 2013). Here we assume a conservative line ratio (in units of $L'$) of $r_{\rm 7-6/1-0} = 0.3$, so $S_{\rm CO(7-6)}^{\rm peak} = 7.1 \, {\rm mJy}$. The [C{\sc i}](2--1) intensity is estimated using the average [C{\sc i}](2--1)/CO(3--2) line ratios of Walter et al. (2011), obtaining: $S_{\rm C{\rm \sc I}}^{\rm peak} = 2.8 \, {\rm mJy}$. The H$_2$O intensity is obtained by using the empirical $L_{\rm H_2O}$--$L_{\rm IR}$ relation of Omont et al. (2013): $S_{\rm H_2O}^{\rm peak} = 1.5 \, {\rm mJy}$. With these values, a 0.10 mJy r.m.s is enough to detected all proposed emission lines at 5$\sigma$ even if the galaxies are resolved into 3 components. Assuming a channel width of 100 km/s (emission lines have $\sim 1000$ km/s FWHM so still able to sample the emission lines with 10 contiguous channels) we need 3.2 h integration on source.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
    </prj:ScienceGoal>
